.TH QDSOUNDING 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-qdtools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
qdsounding \- extract atmospheric soundings from querydata
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qdsounding
.RI [ options ]
.I querydata
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qdsounding
extracts atmospheric soundings from querydata. For point data the
default is to print soundings for every station; for grid data, target
locations must be specified explicitly.
.PP
Option
.B \-P
is required so that scripts cannot rely on a fixed parameter ordering
inside the querydata.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Print the help message.
.TP
.BI \-P " param1,param2,..."
The desired parameters.
.TP
.BI \-w " wmo1,wmo2,..."
WMO station numbers.
.TP
.BI \-p " loc1,loc2,..."
Location names. Coordinate pairs
.IR lon1,lat1,lon2,lat2,...
are also accepted.
.TP
.BI \-x " lon"
Longitude.
.TP
.BI \-y " lat"
Latitude.
.TP
.BI \-t " zone"
Time zone (default
.IR Europe/Helsinki ).
.TP
.BI \-c " file"
Coordinate file.
.TP
.B \-z
Print level value after the level index.
.SH EXAMPLES
Print a temperature/dew-point sounding for a single station:
.PP
.RS 4
qdsounding \-P Temperature,DewPoint \-w 02963 sounding.sqd
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qdsoundingindex (1),
.BR temp2qd (1),
.BR qdpoint (1),
.BR qdinfo (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
